
[1]northerly

   NORTH'ERLY, a. Being towards the north, or nearer towards the north
   than to any other cardinal point. [We use this word and northern with
   considerable latitude.]

   NORTH'ERLY, adv.

   1. Towards the north; as, to sail northerly.

   2. In a northern direction; as a northerly course.

   3. Proceeding from a northern point.
